2.1 Inductive Reasoning from Patterns

Here you'll learn how to inductively draw conclusions from patterns and examples to solve problems.

What if you were given a pattern of three numbers or shapes and asked to determine the sixth number or shape that

fit that pattern? After completing this Concept, you'll be able to use inductive reasoning to draw conclusions like

this based on examples and patterns provided.

